  <span id="freeText4474416277068783335" style="display:none">I had a lot of fun with this book...from his waaay over the top novel within a novel..to the imagined conversations of historical figures..it was a book I was anxious to get back to. Also included was a rather sad piece of family dynamics that the majority of the baby booming generation is currently facing..the aging of ones parents...Its not often one finds historical hilarity, skewering of authors and the publishing game, racial perceptions and stereotypes and family drama all wrapped into one really fine novel. </span>
