        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2749122279" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15569059766283914867">Welcome y’oll to the experiment of intellectual prostitution. Please take a sit and remain quiet during the performance. The nerves of the players have been stretched just enough that they are on the verge of a breakdown from any minute now.<br/>How do you call a book that gives voice to fears so inherent to what you are that it takes time for you to recognize and to distinguish them as not being a part of who you are?<br/>It could not have been a better time for me to read <i>Erasure</i>. It’s not about the for</span>
  <span id="freeText15569059766283914867" style="display:none">Welcome y’oll to the experiment of intellectual prostitution. Please take a sit and remain quiet during the performance. The nerves of the players have been stretched just enough that they are on the verge of a breakdown from any minute now.<br />How do you call a book that gives voice to fears so inherent to what you are that it takes time for you to recognize and to distinguish them as not being a part of who you are?<br />It could not have been a better time for me to read <i>Erasure</i>. It’s not about the form but about the content. It’s about the messages it conveies. It’s a bout foolish dreams and hopes that art can be just art done and brought to its existence by taking in consideration romantic nottions of the pleasure and the throbbing talent yearning to be let out. That so much is about money and so less about essence. That if you want something you have to give something back, and not often the price may be too high. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15569059766283914867" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


