<span id="freeTextContainer3196733439017676363">Percival Everett is the best writer I have encountered in quite some time. I first discovered him through an interview in the Paris Review followed by a review of his newest novel in the NYTimes which led to a trip to my neighborhood bookstore where I picked up his book of short stories, Half and Inch of Water. I devoured that - the stories are smart, intriguing, spare and quite frankly perfect. <br/><br/>Erasure, is funny, heartbreaking, brilliant, angry (but not in the way one would think) and again<br/>perf</span>
  <span id="freeText3196733439017676363" style="display:none">Percival Everett is the best writer I have encountered in quite some time. I first discovered him through an interview in the Paris Review followed by a review of his newest novel in the NYTimes which led to a trip to my neighborhood bookstore where I picked up his book of short stories, Half and Inch of Water. I devoured that - the stories are smart, intriguing, spare and quite frankly perfect. <br /><br />Erasure, is funny, heartbreaking, brilliant, angry (but not in the way one would think) and again<br />perfect.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3196733439017676363" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

